EXTRACTED VALUE: There's something very addictive about taking a mech and doing the Dynasty Warriors thing. [Issue 26, p.98]
Seriously, there's nothing incredible about this. [Aug 2008, p.79]
With levels that redefine “linear,” there is no need to collect objects in a game like this, but that’s mostly what you end up doing.
A brain numbingly dull title that is only partially saved by its above average presentation.
